RACE.RACE_TEXT: Canada Cup Futurity Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Futurity Trial Purse 8000. A FUTURITY TRIAL FOR TWO YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE CANADA QH CUP FUTURITY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY SWEET JESS rallied late stretch, and inched clear. HEZ HOTT UR NOTT jostled away and was oufinished. DJ BRIGHT RUBY broke outward and closed late. ST PADDY 109 was fractious then dismounted the rider at the gate, bumped leaving, rallied inside, and weakened late. NOT EASY BEING ME brushed leaving, and lacked a serious bid. HI HOPES showed little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Canada Cup Futurity Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 2 400 Y Dirt CR: 75. Futurity Trial Purse 8000. A FUTURITY TRIAL FOR TWO YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE CANADA QH CUP FUTURITY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIMBERS BEAUTY dug in late and won the nod. HORTONS TRUTH almost lasted. BDB SEIS HOT TAMALE raced evenly. MOUNTAIN NIGHT TRAIN ducked in sharply and trailed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Canada Cup Futurity Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 3 400 Y Dirt CR: 79. Futurity Trial Purse 8000. A FUTURITY TRIAL FOR TWO YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE CANADA QH CUP FUTURITY. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BITTERROOTS WAGON easy winner. FIRED flew late. WINKINS WAGON BOSS weakened late. O LETS BE FIRST drifted in leaving the chute, and yielding late. MISS FANCY NANCY broke out into MS MINI WARRIOR, steadied leaving the chute, and gave best late. MS MINI WARRIOR bumped leaving the gate, and retreated. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race but made no change after a review of the film. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection was lodged by the rider of MISS FANCY NANCY alleging interference leaving the chute was not allowed.

ENTRY.NAME: Bitterroots Wagon
ENTRY.OWNER: Stockwell Buckey A and Wills Glenn K

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Canada Cup Derby CENTURY DOWNS RACE 4 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Derby Trial Purse 8000. A DERBY TRIAL FOR 3 YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE CANADA QH CUP DERBY. See AQHRA Stakes book for conditions. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOBLE REARING quickly went to the front, and held safely. MS CLARA rallied determinedly outside, getting by to earn place. KARI L CARTEL bested late for place. SPRINGELEER angled inside leaving the chute, and flattened. APPRECIATE late bid. NAUGHTEE OR NICE broke inward, and weakened late. DECIDER CARTEL QUEEN failed to threaten. TRAINER OBJECTION- An objection was lodged by the trainer of SPRINGELEER against the rider of NOBLE REARING alleging interference leaving the chute was not allowed.

ENTRY.NAME: Ms Clara
ENTRY.OWNER: Wippert Jr Harold and Wippert Arlene

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Canada Cup Derby Trial CENTURY DOWNS RACE 5 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Derby Trial Purse 8000. A DERBY TRIAL FOR 3 YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSES WHO NOMINATED AND REMAIN ELIGIBLE FOR THE CANADA QH CUP DERBY. See AQHRA Stakes book for conditions. Weight 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROFESSOR GEE quickest leaving the chute, and held firm under a late drive. NORTHFORK BOSS was out finished after a determined effort. TULSA TIMBER closed late to earn show. HEZA MAJESTIC HERO gave best late. EYEMADASHIN yielded in the late stages. JAMEZ BOND broke into NASHVILLE STARR, and lacked a bid. NASHVILLE STARR bumped leaving and was unable to recover from the start.

ENTRY.NAME: Northfork Boss
ENTRY.OWNER: Wills Glenn Stockwell Buckey A and Gehring Delton D

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 78. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS IN THEIR LAST THREE STARTS AND HAVE NOT WON A STARTER SINCE STARING FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS OR OPTIONAL CL AIMING $12,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGICAL LADY contested the early pace outside of GO MAMA then sat just off the lead into the backstretch, edged clear of rival, and just held under a late threat by ADDYDIDIT. ADDYDIDIT unhurried early, gained quickly through the final turn, drove between deep stretch and just missed. GO MAMA vied inside for the early lead, led the way through the backstretch then took pressure in the far turn, was overtaken, and gave way grudgingly late. HENRY'S GAMBLE tracked the pacesetters from the two path, chased through the final turn, and lacked the kick needed. SKY DESTINY trailed the field, and passed tiring. LITTLE HARPER raced four wide entering the front side, and faded gradually.

ENTRY.NAME: Go Mama
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, took pressure, gave way grudgingly

ENTRY.NAME: Magical Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: contested pace, edged clear, just held

ENTRY.NAME: Henry's Gamble
ENTRY.OWNER: Elsener Terry Brown James R and Konyk Jr Bill

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOOL TIME was quickest to the turn, disposed of rival nearing the final turn, drew clear into the stretch, and held safely. BORKAN stalked three-wide entering in the far turn then dropped back, gained closer order leaving the backstretch but was no match for the winner in the stretch. MUCHO MAGIC unhurried early, angled out to the three path into the stretch, and edged clear to secure a third-place finish. SCHOCHOH fanned three-wide in the opening turn, and closed gradually. ESTIFRAAD trailed early and bid belatedly. COMMON KNOWLEDGE broke inward then was sent for speed, pressed the pace through the backstretch, and gave way in the stretch. DAD'S LEGACY lacked a clear path leaving, and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Tool Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed, drew clear, held safely

ENTRY.NAME: Estifraad
ENTRY.OWNER: Tornado Racing and Frey Racing Stable

ENTRY.NAME: Borkan
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3w, dropped back, gained, no match for winner

ENTRY.NAME: Schochoh
ENTRY.OWNER: Poitras Racing Stable and O'Hagan Colleen

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Cl aiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAKE CHARGE GWEN fanned three wide into the opening, took closer order leaving the backstretch, gained a narrow advantage into the stretch, was kept under handling, and edged away. WHEELSUPINTHIRTY chased the pace through the backstretch, rallied between into the stretch, and was out-finished. EDGE OF OKOTOKS sped to the front then opened up to good margins into the backstretch, was joined into the final turn then was run down. WILD ARCH trailed the field and closed steadily last missing out. MISTY MATT lost ground leaving the opening turn, lodged a rail bid but was unable to improve position. DAZZLING CHIC saved to no avail. KISSABLE U chased five wide, and tired. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of WHEELSUPINTHIRTY against the rider of TAKE CHARGE GWEN alleging interference in the stretch was not allowed.TIMER MALFUNCTION- The race was hand-timed due to a timer malfunction.

ENTRY.NAME: Misty Matt
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, rail bid, no improve

ENTRY.NAME: Take Charge Gwen
ENTRY.OWNER: Profect Jay Freeman Carrie Robertson Jerri R and Hardy Lesley

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: J. D. Squires & M. A. Squires

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000 (Lesser Claiming Races For $3,500 ($4,500) at Century Mile/Down s Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKY HALO saved ground while setting the pace, responded to pressure in the final turn, was kept under steady encouragement and just held after a long drive. SHAKINOFFTHERUST sat just off the pace from the three path, was roused at the head of the stretch, rallied determinedly outside, and narrowly missed. REBATE stalked from the rail, lodged a rail bid, and lacked room deep stretch. STUBBORN LOVE fanned three wide into the opening turn, gained outside into the far turn, and lacked the rally needed in the drive. ANNA'S IMAGE saved inside and failed to threaten. VALENTINO ROSSA raced three wide in the first turn, and lacked a serious bid. DRAMATIC FLAIR offered little. WICKED WIZZY lacked interest. STARLIGHT LANE sat mid-pack and was done early.

ENTRY.NAME: Rebate
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, rail bid, lacked room

ENTRY.NAME: Shakinofftherust
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3w, roused, rallied determinedly, narrowly missed
